Here's a clean implementation using the MVVM Community Toolkit:

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace YourApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        if (IsBusy) return;

        try
        {
            IsBusy = true;

            // Replace with your actual data service call
            var product = await FetchProductAsync();

            Name = product.Name;
            Price = product.Price;
            IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget Pro", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` source-generates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, etc.) with `INotifyPropertyChanged` built in — no manual `OnPropertyChanged` calls needed.
- `[RelayCommand]` generates a `LoadCommand` (IAsyncRelayCommand) you can bind to buttons/page lifecycle.
- `IsBusy` lets you show an `ActivityIndicator` and prevent duplicate loads.

**XAML binding example:**

```xml
<Label Text="{Binding Name}" />
<Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
<Switch IsToggled="{Binding IsAvailable, Mode=OneWay}" />
<Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
<ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}" IsVisible="{Binding IsBusy}" />
```

**NuGet required:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0).
